      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOLD AND BROWN (4) caught the eye on debut when showed strong early dash and proved too slick around this track over 400m in 22.66, scoring by 1.3 lengths. Looks above average and expected to go close again. KING ZEAL (6) is a promising dog in the frame at five of nine starts including three wins and was in the minors again latest (22.89) over 400m at this track. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from three starts. Expected to feature on best form. ALWAYS THE SUN (1) last raced on March 3 when fourth (25.91) over 457m at Q Lakeside in a Grade 5. Has a good overall strike-rate and can find the frame here. SIDE SHOW BOB (2) can improve on an unplaced run here last time out.",
